#. <section class="sutta" id="an10.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.2:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Ānisaṃsavagga"
msgstr "1. Benefits"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Cetanākaraṇīyasutta"
msgstr "2. Making a Wish"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an10.2:1.1"
msgid "“Sīlavato, bhikkhave, sīlasampannassa na cetanāya karaṇīyaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, an ethical person, who has fulfilled ethical conduct, need not "
"make a wish:"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.2"
msgid "‘avippaṭisāro me uppajjatū’ti."
msgstr "‘May I have no regrets!’"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.3"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yaṃ sīlavato sīlasampannassa avippaṭisāro uppajjati."
msgstr "It’s only natural that an ethical person has no regrets."

msgctxt "an10.2:1.4"
msgid "Avippaṭisārissa, bhikkhave, na cetanāya karaṇīyaṃ:"
msgstr "When you have no regrets you need not make a wish:"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.5"
msgid "‘pāmojjaṃ me uppajjatū’ti."
msgstr "‘May I feel joy!’"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.6"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yaṃ avippaṭisārissa pāmojjaṃ jāyati."
msgstr "It’s only natural that joy springs up when you have no regrets."

msgctxt "an10.2:1.7"
msgid "Pamuditassa, bhikkhave, na cetanāya karaṇīyaṃ:"
msgstr "When you feel joy you need not make a wish:"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.8"
msgid "‘pīti me uppajjatū’ti."
msgstr "‘May I experience rapture!’"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.9"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yaṃ pamuditassa pīti uppajjati."
msgstr "It’s only natural that rapture arises when you’re joyful."

msgctxt "an10.2:1.10"
msgid "Pītimanassa, bhikkhave, na cetanāya karaṇīyaṃ:"
msgstr "When your mind is full of rapture you need not make a wish:"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.11"
msgid "‘kāyo me passambhatū’ti."
msgstr "‘May my body become tranquil!’"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.12"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yaṃ pītimanassa kāyo passambhati."
msgstr ""
"It’s only natural that your body becomes tranquil when your mind is full of "
"rapture."

msgctxt "an10.2:1.13"
msgid "Passaddhakāyassa, bhikkhave, na cetanāya karaṇīyaṃ:"
msgstr "When your body is tranquil you need not make a wish:"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.14"
msgid "‘sukhaṃ vediyāmī’ti."
msgstr "‘May I feel bliss!’"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.15"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yaṃ passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vediyati."
msgstr "It’s only natural to feel bliss when your body is tranquil."

msgctxt "an10.2:1.16"
msgid "Sukhino, bhikkhave, na cetanāya karaṇīyaṃ:"
msgstr "When you feel bliss you need not make a wish:"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.17"
msgid "‘cittaṃ me samādhiyatū’ti."
msgstr "‘May my mind be immersed in samādhi!’"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.18"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yaṃ sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"It’s only natural for the mind to be immersed in samādhi when you feel bliss."

msgctxt "an10.2:1.19"
msgid "Samāhitassa, bhikkhave, na cetanāya karaṇīyaṃ:"
msgstr "When your mind is immersed in samādhi you need not make a wish:"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.20"
msgid "‘yathābhūtaṃ jānāmi passāmī’ti."
msgstr "‘May I truly know and see!’"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.21"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yaṃ samāhito yathābhūtaṃ jānāti passati."
msgstr ""
"It’s only natural to truly know and see when your mind is immersed in "
"samādhi."

msgctxt "an10.2:1.22"
msgid "Yathābhūtaṃ, bhikkhave, jānato passato na cetanāya karaṇīyaṃ:"
msgstr "When you truly know and see you need not make a wish:"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.23"
msgid "‘nibbindāmi virajjāmī’ti."
msgstr "‘May I become disillusioned and dispassionate!’"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.24"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yaṃ yathābhūtaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ nibbindati virajjati."
msgstr ""
"It’s only natural to become disillusioned and dispassionate when you truly "
"know and see."

#. VAR: Nibbinnassa → nibbindassa (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an10.2:1.25"
msgid "Nibbinnassa, bhikkhave, virattassa na cetanāya karaṇīyaṃ:"
msgstr "When you’re disillusioned and dispassionate you need not make a wish:"

msgctxt "an10.2:1.26"
msgid "‘vimuttiñāṇadassanaṃ sacchikaromī’ti."
msgstr "‘May I realize the knowledge and vision of freedom!’"

#. VAR: nibbinno → nibbiṇṇo (bj) | nibbindo (si, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an10.2:1.27"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yaṃ nibbinno viratto vimuttiñāṇadassanaṃ "
"sacchikaroti."
msgstr ""
"It’s only natural to realize the knowledge and vision of freedom when you’re "
"disillusioned and dispassionate."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an10.2:2.1"
msgid ""
"Iti kho, bhikkhave, nibbidāvirāgo vimuttiñāṇadassanattho "
"vimuttiñāṇadassanānisaṃso;"
msgstr ""
"And so, mendicants, the knowledge and vision of freedom is the purpose and "
"benefit of disillusionment and dispassion."

msgctxt "an10.2:2.2"
msgid "yathābhūtañāṇadassanaṃ nibbidāvirāgatthaṃ nibbidāvirāgānisaṃsaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Disillusionment and dispassion is the purpose and benefit of truly knowing "
"and seeing."

msgctxt "an10.2:2.3"
msgid "samādhi yathābhūtañāṇadassanattho yathābhūtañāṇadassanānisaṃso;"
msgstr "Truly knowing and seeing is the purpose and benefit of immersion."

msgctxt "an10.2:2.4"
msgid "sukhaṃ samādhatthaṃ samādhānisaṃsaṃ;"
msgstr "Immersion is the purpose and benefit of bliss."

msgctxt "an10.2:2.5"
msgid "passaddhi sukhatthā sukhānisaṃsā;"
msgstr "Bliss is the purpose and benefit of tranquility."

msgctxt "an10.2:2.6"
msgid "pīti passaddhatthā passaddhānisaṃsā;"
msgstr "Tranquility is the purpose and benefit of rapture."

msgctxt "an10.2:2.7"
msgid "pāmojjaṃ pītatthaṃ pītānisaṃsaṃ;"
msgstr "Rapture is the purpose and benefit of joy."

msgctxt "an10.2:2.8"
msgid "avippaṭisāro pāmojjattho pāmojjānisaṃso;"
msgstr "Joy is the purpose and benefit of not having regrets."

msgctxt "an10.2:2.9"
msgid "kusalāni sīlāni avippaṭisāratthāni avippaṭisārānisaṃsāni."
msgstr "Not having regrets is the purpose and benefit of skillful ethics."

msgctxt "an10.2:2.10"
msgid ""
"Iti kho, bhikkhave, dhammā dhamme abhisandenti, dhammā dhamme paripūrenti "
"apārā pāraṃ gamanāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"And so, mendicants, good qualities flow on and fill up from one to the "
"other, for going from the near shore to the far shore.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.2:2.11"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
